# Project Name
CougDirect (WSU ROAR- VR APPLICATION)
## Project summary
WSU ROAR is a program at WSU for students with mental disabilities. Our project is run through this program, and we intend to design a mobile application for
these students to help them navigate the WSU campus. We plan to help them by letting them indicate which WSU buildings, and other locations they would like to go to, 
and then it will help them with directions, as well as first person videos and 360 tours of each building. The user will be able to make a path of multiple locations on campus
that will help them find their way. 
### One-sentence description of the project
Mobile Application with VR capabilities to help students navigate their way around the WSU campus. 

### Additional information about the project
The user will include a video series of walking tours of campus, as well as VR capable tours of indoor locations on campus.
